Protests flared up in the area this week related tensions between rival taxi groups. CAPE TOWN - Law enforcement officials will continue monitoring a section of Prince George Drive near Muizenberg on Thursday morning. Protests flared up in the area this week related tensions between rival taxi groups. A group of protesters gathered in the area on Thursday morning but have since dispersed. The city s Maxine Bezuidenhout says: All roads along Prince George Drive have been reopened. Law enforcement agencies are currently monitoring the area. Approximately 30 protesters were detained and taken to subs. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)